Class TypeDefinitions

java.lang.Object
org.microbean.clientproxy.bytebuddy.TypeDefinitions
public final class TypeDefinitions extends Object
A provider of TypeDefinitions backed by a TypePool, which is normally a TypeElementTypePool.
Author:
Laird Nelson

      public final TypeDescription typeDescription(TypeMirror t)

    • typeDescription

      public final TypeDescription typeDescription(String typePoolName)
      Returns a non-null TypeDescription for a type pool name.

      The structure and format of type pool names are not fully documented and defined only by Byte Buddy's internal implementation.

      Parameters:
      typePoolName - a type pool name; must not be null
      Returns:
      a non-null TypeDescription
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if typePoolName is null
      TypePool.Resolution.NoSuchTypeException - if there is no suitable TypeDescription
      See Also:
      • TypePool.describe(String)
      • TypePool.Resolution.resolve()

    • typeDescriptionGeneric

      public final TypeDescription.Generic typeDescriptionGeneric(TypeMirror t)
      Returns a non-null TypeDescription.Generic for a TypeMirror.
      Parameters:
      t - a TypeMirror; must be an array, primitive, void, wildcard, or reference type
      Returns:
      a non-null TypeDescription.Generic
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if t is null
      IllegalArgumentException - if t is not a suitable type
